Hi, Jack.

9
00:00:20,388 --> 00:00:22,226
- I'm Juliet.
- Where are my friends?

10
00:00:24,200 --> 00:00:26,077
Tell me where my friends are!

11
00:02:32,317 --> 00:02:34,177
My husband says it's time to leave.

12
00:02:35,780 --> 00:02:38,106
He doesn't think Jack
and the others are coming.

13
00:02:38,418 --> 00:02:40,549
It's been over a day
since we lit the fire.

14
00:02:41,474 --> 00:02:42,764
They should be here by now.

15
00:02:42,901 --> 00:02:44,288
Jack knows we're out here.

16
00:02:44,718 --> 00:02:46,419
He's counting on our signal.

17
00:02:54,621 --> 00:02:56,536
Perhaps he's not able to see the smoke.

18
00:02:56,818 --> 00:02:59,319
If he's north of us,
the mountains would block his view.

19
00:03:00,160 --> 00:03:01,899
We need to sail forward along the coast,

20
00:03:01,987 --> 00:03:04,293
Clear the mountains
and start another signal fire.

21
00:03:11,215 --> 00:03:12,915
I told Jack I would light a fire.

22
00:03:13,345 --> 00:03:14,654
I'm not abandoning him.

23
00:03:31,791 --> 00:03:33,941
My husband thinks
we have to do as he says,

24
00:03:34,492 --> 00:03:36,818
Because he's the only one
who knows how to sail.

25
00:03:38,943 --> 00:03:40,175
But he's wrong.

26
00:03:43,578 --> 00:03:44,985
I can help you sail the boat.

27
00:04:06,577 --> 00:04:07,828
Are you feeling any better?

28
00:04:14,271 --> 00:04:15,640
I made the soup myself,

29
00:04:16,865 --> 00:04:19,348
